data.content:
noun
plural ~ ends
[count] :a part of something (such as a job or story) that has not been completed
We still have one more loose end to deal with before we're finished with the project.
usually plural
The project is almost complete, but we still have a few loose ends to tie up.
All the story's loose ends were wrapped up as the novel ended.
at loose ends
US or Brit at a loose end
not knowing what to do :not having anything in particular to do
With everyone on vacation she was at loose ends.
Drop by if you find yourself at loose ends this weekend.
